name: Ragnar Trail Zion - UT
intro:
Hit the trails and leave the world behind at Ragnar Trail Zion-UT presented by Salomon on May 12-13, 2017. Teams of 8 (or 4) will find their inner wild on three different gritty trails that start and finish at Ragnar Village. The adventure starts on Friday at Zion Ponderosa Ranch, a trail running Shangri-li that sits on 8,000 pristine acres of land, bordering Zion National Park. Runners will experience the vast Southern Utah desert landscape as they meander through juniper and pine trees on their way to new plateaus. Dixie National Forest, Cedar Breaks, and Zion National Park’s famous “Checkerboard” can all be seen from the course. Ragnar Village provides yoga, bonfires, s’mores, music, entertainment and a party atmosphere that Ragnarians have come to love. 

Ragnar Trail Zion-UT is part of the Double Medal Series. Conquer Ragnar Trail Zion-UT and Reebok Ragnar Wasatch Back in 2017, and earn a new double medal! 

All 2016 Zion participants who Captain a team in 2017 will receive a free Ragnar edition Cotopaxi Luzon daypack when you register with promo code ZT17MPACK. No expiration. Cannot be combined with other offers. Daypacks delivered to Captains at the race.

village:
Ragnar Village is the heart and soul of the Ragnar Trail Relay. Each trail loop begins and ends in the Ragnar Village. It is the start line, the finish line, and the exchange point. After each loop you will return to the support of your teammates and the adulation of the teams around you.

  • Bonfire, s'mores
  • Free coffee and hot chocolate Friday night starting at sunset until 11am Saturday morning (while supplies last)
  • 6 yoga sessions (bring your own mat)
  • Massage: Free 8 minute sports massages. $1 per minute for any additional time. Please bring cash.
  • Food sales
  • 1 Free Meal per registered runner (Friday night dinner)
  • Beer Garden Sales
  • Recreation Barn FREE activities (volleyball, horseshoes, ping pong, pool, foosball).
  • Recreation Barn activites with fee: Climbing wall, trampoline bungee, mini golf.
  • Hot Showers (12 units only)
  • 1 pool, 2 hot tubs (no lifeguards on duty)
  • Games and giveaways
  • Ragnar Swag available at the Merch Tent
  • Movies
  • Billions of stars

 

Team Campsite

Each team may choose where to set up their team campsite in the camping area. Teams will be allowed to drive up to the camping area and unload their gear. Vehicles will be parked 5 miles down the road and drivers will be shuttled back to the camping area. Awards will be given for the best decorated team campsite and almost anything goes: tents, canopies, camping chairs, kiddie pools full of Kool-Aid, whatever. For more information on your team's campsite please see the Travel & Lodging page.

meta_description: Hit the trails and leave the world behind at Ragnar Trail Zion-UT presented by Salomon on May 12-13, 2017. Teams of 8 (or 4) will find their inner wild on three different gritty trails that start and finish at Ragnar Village. The adventure starts on Friday at Zion Ponderosa Ranch, a trail running Shangri-la that sits on 8,000 pristine acres of land, bordering Zion National Park.

legs.name: Green Loop - Checkerboard view
legs.description: After leaving Ragnar Village on a dirt road you will quickly connect onto a single-track trail. This trail will connect you to single track bike and horse trails that will take you on a journey out to a beautiful view of Checkerboard in Zion National Park. You will then be on a rollercoaster ride on single track trail that gets a bit narrow so watch your footing! It wouldn't be a Ragnar if we didn't challenge you when you are dead tired at the end of your loop. So we added a few switchbacks that will take you up to the tree camping area. You will wind your way around and then meet up with the Yellow and Red Loops and make it a race back to the Village!

legs.name: Yellow Loop - Pine Knoll
legs.description: Don't blink, You don't want to miss anything on this leg. The first mile provides panoramic views of Zion Ponderosa Ranch. At the beginning of the second mile you will encounter a scenic single track trail that climbs 400 ft. along a pristine ridge. Dig deep to get the the top where you will be rewarded with amazing vistas of Zion National Park! Once you have taken enough pictures you will then be on a downhill journey that twists and turns back to Ragnar Village. Enjoy!!

legs.name: Red Loop - Backbone
legs.description: This trail begins immediately with single track horse trail that will soon connect with an ATV trail. You will cross paths with the yellow loop and continue up the trail through the trees, gaining 400 feet in about a mile and half. Keep on going and dig deeper cause this loop is not an easy one! The ATV trail will keep going up up up! Pay attention to the signs as you will make a sharp right onto a single track trail and you will be on a roller coaster ride for about a mile through the pines going over several bridges. Watch your step! You will be rewarded with beautiful views of Zion National Park so bring your camera! Once you are off the single track it's all downhill from here! But you are only at the halfway mark. Be sure to fill up at the water station and hydrate before finishing up the final few miles on double track, road and some single track before returning to the Village.

travel.content:
Directions

Recommended directions to Zion Ponderosa Ranch can be found HERE. The closest major airports include Salt Lake City, UT or Las Vegas, NV.

Should you decide to travel through Zion National Park, the U.S. National Park Service will be assessing a $30 entrance fee that will be valid for 7 days.

 

Parking and Gear Drop

Thursday and Friday Arrival: When you arrive to Zion Ponderosa Ranch you will follow signs and volunteer directions to the drop off zones located in the camping areas. You will unload all of your gear, QUICKLY, and go find a campsite. Your driver will follow signs and volunteer direction out of the ranch and to the parking area 5 miles down the road. The drivers will then be shuttled back to the ranch.

  • Arrival time on Thursday is between 4-11pm, NO EXCEPTIONS. You will not be admitted entry outside of these hours unless you have a lodging reservation. 
  •  Anyone arriving Friday evening after shuttle hours will follow signs and volunteer direction to parking that will be within walking distance of the village.
  • Volunteers staying temporarily for their shift will be able to park in our designated volunteer parking area close to the village and will need to remove their car as soon as their shift is finished. Any volunteers staying for the entire event can follow the same procedure as the teams.

Saturday Departure: Drivers will be shuttled out to the parking area. They will then drive back to the camping area in their own vehicles and pick up their team (who will be ready and waiting) and gear at the designated pick up locations, QUICKLY, and head on home! If you are staying until Sunday we will have you shuttle your car back to your campsite by 6:00pm on Saturday.

 

Shuttle Hours

Thursday – 4:00pm-11:00pm (Last shuttle will leave venue at 10:45)
Friday – 8:00am – 5:00pm
Saturday – 9:00am – 6:00pm

 

Camping

Camping on Friday night in the Ragnar Village is included in your registration fee. This includes camping for all of your team and support crew (family and friends). 

Thursday night camping is available for $10 per person (charged by Zion Ponderosa). This will be collected upon arrival. Cash is preferred and will make for shorter lines. Saturday night camping is also available for an additional $10 per person.

Teams may select their campsite upon arrival (first come, first served). We ask you to try and keep your campsite to 300 square-feet/ 17' x 17'. There is no need to contact ZPR for campsite accommodations for Thursday-Saturday night. However, if you plan to come earlier or stay later, please call ZPR for a campsite reservation.

Vehicles will be allowed in the village for a speedy drop off so make sure everything is packed in bags and ready to be unloaded. Awards will be given for the best decorated team campsite and almost anything goes: tents, canopies, camping chairs, kiddie pools full of Kool-Aid, whatever.

Check out a map of the camping areas and figure out where your team wants to camp at the race. Do you want to be closer to the action or be tucked away somewhere quiet?

Don’t know what to pack? Check out our packing guide.

 

Rental Equipment

For those teams that are flying in and don't want to haul gear, Zion Ponderosa Ranch has a limited amount of rental equipment (tents and sleeping bags). Call for availability: 1-800-293-5444

 

 

Lodging/RV

Call 1-800-293-5444 to book a house, cabin or RV spot. IF YOU DO NOT HAVE AN RV RESERVATION YOU MAY NOT BRING YOUR RV. TRAILERS OF ANY KIND ARE NOT ALLOWED AT VENUE UNLESS YOU HAVE MADE A RESERVATION.

 

Sustainability

Ragnar seeks ways to reduce the carbon footprint of our races. We ask that you join us in this effort by carpooling on your drive to the race and striving to bring only two (2) vehicles per team.
